snippet: A judge has dismissed lawsuits that sought to block the New York Public Library from renovating its flagship Fifth Avenue branch under a plan that the library has already largely scuttled.
abstract: A judge has dismissed lawsuits that sought to block the New York Public Library from renovating its flagship Fifth Avenue branch under a plan that the library has already largely scuttled.

headline.main: Judge Dismisses Legal Challenges to Defunct Library Plan
headline.print_headline: Judge Rejects Challenges To Defunct Library Plan
